
Solvenzregulierung, Kapitalanlage und Überschussverteilung – Ein größenabhängiger Vergleich des Marktverhaltens deutscher Lebensversicherer




 
© 2015, Springer-Verlag Berlin Heidelberg. Solvency II increases the capital requirements in the life insurance industry. Preparing for the new regulatory regime, life insurers have resorted to different strategies: investments, profit participation and capitalization vary systematically by size. In particular small insurers without access to capital markets have accumulated fresh capital by cutting profit participation and dividend payouts while simultaneously following conservative investment strategies. Solvency II is thus not neutral to size but biases against small life insurers that respond by adversely affecting current stakeholders to get fit for the new regulatory setting.


